      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'll modify the query to use parameterized queries, which are safer and more efficient. This will also make it easier to avoid the scanner's issues.\n\n```python\nimport sqlite3\n\ndef login_user(username, password):\n    conn = sqlite3.connect('users.db')\n    cursor = conn.cursor()\n    \n    query = \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = ? AND password = ?\"\n    cursor.execute(query, (username, password))\n    user = cursor.fetchone()\n    \n    if user:\n        return True\n    else:\n        return False\n```\n\nBy using parameterized queries, we're telling the database to treat the username and password as parameters, rather than literal strings. This makes it much harder for the scanner to flag the query as vulnerable to SQL injection attacks.",
